El bloqueo automtico permite sacar los cables de red solo presionando el botn de bloqueo. Por lo tanto, sus dispositivos permanecen conectados a Internet o a la red de datos incluso cuando se mueve.

Disfruta de velocidades de transferencia de hasta 10 Gbps.

Es 10 veces ms rpido que los cables de red Cat6 de uso comn.

El blindaje (S/FTP / PIMF).

Cable: Clase de blindaje: S/FTP (PiMF). Especificaciones: Conductor interior CAT 7. Material: CU (cobre).

  • Indicacin de longitud en la boquilla protectora Slimline.

FootballPlayingKitten
5,0 de 5 estrellas Good though not best value over CAT6a
Revisado en Reino Unido el 13 de septiembre de 2019
Tamao: 1 mColor: Negro - 5 piezasCompra verificada
If you're running 10Gbe in say a local cluster (with a view to upgrade to 25/40Gbe at some point soon) and want good quality CAT6a/CU+ and not CCA (despite short distance) then this cable does work well: while CAT7 for some reason it is cheaper than the "proper CAT6A" from the same vendor. Otherwise I would have got CAT6A.

It's S/FTP (naturally) and AWG26 (CU?) while CAT6A cable seems to be AWG27-CCA unless you pay more for "proper" AWG27/CU. Note that CAT6 seems to be AWG28-CCA these days when originally you used to get AWG27/CU.

It's pretty thick and not easily routable and about as thick as POE/AWG24-CAT5e/CAT6 external cable but I guess due to the shielding it cannot be helped.

For 1Gbe then I would not bother but if you wanted proper CU decent AWG cable (26-27) that won't be cheap thus may as well get CAT7 even though it's not needed. I would not replace CU CAT6/6A with CAT7 in any case.
